---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="work-detail">
  <main id="main">
    <!-- HEADER + COVER -->
    <section class="wd-cover">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="wd-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Case Study · 2025</div>
          <h1>Sora Landing Kit.</h1>
          <p class="section-lede">
            A modular landing page kit we built for a founder mid-sprint. From
            research and design system to handoff in 3 weeks.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="wd-cover-frame pat-arcs pattern-wrap" aria-hidden="true">
        </div>

        <div class="wd-meta-grid">
          <div>
            <div class="k">Year</div>
            <div class="v">2025</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="k">Client</div>
            <div class="v">Sora.io</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="k">Duration</div>
            <div class="v">3 weeks</div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="k">Service</div>
            <div class="v">Web Design + Dev</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 01 CONTEXT -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="wd-section">
          <div class="eyebrow">01 · Context</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">What we were facing.</h2>
          <p>
            Sora is a B2B SaaS product that had just raised a seed round. Their
            MVP was ready, but the landing page was still a free Webflow
            template with generic copywriting, and they were pushing for a
            Series A pitch in 2 months.
          </p>
          <p>
            The team was small (4 people), no designer, and no bandwidth to
            maintain a complex page. What they needed: a landing that converts,
            looks serious, but is easy to update themselves without a dev team.
          </p>

          <div class="wd-quote">
            <em>"We need to look like a team of 20, but we&rsquo;re only 4."</em
            >
            <span class="cite">— Founder, Sora.io</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 02 APPROACH -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="wd-section">
          <div class="eyebrow">02 · Approach</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">How we started.</h2>
          <p>
            We began by auditing competitor landing pages and their brand. Three
            insights emerged: the copy was too corporate, the hero had no clear
            proposition, and there were too many CTAs (8 on one page).
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Reduce sections from 11 to 6 essentials</li>
            <li>
              Rewrite hero copy with the founder, focused on 1 value proposition
            </li>
            <li>Build in Framer so the Sora team can edit copy themselves</li>
            <li>Set up an A/B test for hero variants in the first week live</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 03 EXECUTION -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="wd-section">
          <div class="eyebrow">03 · Execution</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">From wireframe to live.</h2>
          <p>
            Wireframe → visual design → Framer build, all in parallel. A
            30-minute review at the end of each week kept direction aligned.
            Typography was Geist + Söhne for display, palette limited to 5
            colors.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="wd-gallery">
          <div class="frame pat-grid pattern-wrap" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="frame pat-stripe pattern-wrap" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="frame wide pat-block pattern-wrap" aria-hidden="true">
          </div>
          <div class="frame pat-confetti pattern-wrap" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div class="frame pat-arcs pattern-wrap" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 04 RESULTS -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="wd-section">
          <div class="eyebrow">04 · Results</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">What changed after launch.</h2>
          <p>
            Two weeks post-launch, conversion rate rose significantly and bounce
            rate dropped because visitors understood who the product was for,
            faster. The Sora team also reported that demo requests coming in
            were far more qualified.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="wd-metrics">
          <div class="wd-metric">
            <div class="k">Conversion Rate</div>
            <div class="v">+120%</div>
            <div class="lbl">Visitor → demo request</div>
          </div>
          <div class="wd-metric">
            <div class="k">Bounce Rate</div>
            <div class="v">−40%</div>
            <div class="lbl">More visitors scrolling &gt; 50%</div>
          </div>
          <div class="wd-metric">
            <div class="k">Client Score</div>
            <div class="v">
              4.8<span style="font-size:.5em; opacity:.6;">/5</span>
            </div>
            <div class="lbl">Based on post-project survey</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 05 CREDITS -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="wd-section">
          <div class="eyebrow">05 · Credits</div>
          <h2 class="section-title">Team &amp; tools.</h2>
          <div
            class="wd-meta-grid"
            style="border-top:0; margin-top:0; padding-top:0;"
          >
            <div>
              <div class="k">Design</div>
              <div class="v">Roha Studio</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="k">Development</div>
              <div class="v">Framer</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="k">Client</div>
              <div class="v">Sora.io</div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="k">Year</div>
              <div class="v">2025</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- NEXT PROJECT -->
    <section class="section-tight">
      <div class="cta-wrap">
        <a href="/work" class="wd-next">
          <div>
            <div class="label">Next Project · 2026</div>
            <h3>Nimbus Dashboard</h3>
          </div>
          <span class="arr" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
